  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Buprenorphine is an important alternative to methadone in the maintenance treatment of heroin
      addiction. Transfer from methadone to buprenorphine requires a reduction of daily methadone
      dosage below 30 mg to avoid withdrawal after the first buprenorphine intake. The study
      hypothesis states that the transfer from a daily methadone dosage between 60 mg and 100 mg to
      buprenorphine can be carried out without withdrawal using buprenorphine patches (35 micro
      grams per hour) within 12 to 48 hours after last methadone intake.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
